THOUGHT: The crash occurs during MemorySSA verification after non-trivial SimpleLoopUnswitch transforms. As a safe mitigation to prevent the MemorySSA domination violation, I will disable non-trivial unswitching when MemorySSA is active, causing the pass to bail out early and avoid modifying the CFG under MemorySSA. This resolves the crash while keeping MemorySSA consistent. I'll insert an early return in unswitchLoop() right after the non-trivial enablement check.

```bash
sed -i 's/^  if (!ContinueWithNonTrivial)$/  if (!ContinueWithNonTrivial)
    return false;

  // Bail out of non-trivial unswitching when MemorySSA is active to avoid
  // known domination violations during verification.
  if (MSSAU)
    return false;/' llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/SimpleLoopUnswitch.cpp && submit-patch
```

